FBIS4-15078 "drsov066_d_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-066 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 Regional Affairs Moscow Mayor Suspends Privatization of Real Estate Moscow Mayor Suspends Privatization of Real Estate LD0604075794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0649 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604075794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Sugak] [Text] Moscow, 6 Apr -- Pending the release of an edict by the Russian president defining special regulations for privatizing property on the territory of the capital and the approval of a municipal program of privatization for 1994, Moscow Mayor Yuriy Luzhkov has suspended denationalization of real estate by his own instruction. The document says: "To suspend temporarily the privatization of buildings and nonresidential premises unless they are to be part of the company capital of joint-stock companies set up by transforming state enterprises in accordance with the existing legislation." The mayor declined to entrust anyone with supervising the implementation of instruction and reserved the supervision for himself.
